Title: Tachyon Condensation and Black Hole Entropy
Authors: Atish Dabholkar
Comments: 4 pages, Revtex
Report-no: HUPT-01/A051, TIFR/TH/01-42
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 88 (2002) 091301
\\
  String propagation on a cone with deficit angle $2\pi(1-{1\over N})$ is
considered for the purpose of computing the entropy of a large mass black hole.
The entropy computed using the recent results on condensation of twisted-sector
tachyons in this theory is found to be in precise agreement with the
Bekenstein-Hawking entropy.
